Restricted Data Use Agreement

By downloading this data, you agree to the Terms of Use set forth by the SRSS project and Dataverse. Failure to comply with these regulations may result in account termination and/or legal action.
• You will ensure that the data will be stored on a password‐protected computer on a secure server.
• Passwords must be managed and changed at least once a year.
• If using a portable device such as a laptop or tablet, data must be stored securely and proper encryption procedures must be followed (i.e., including a bitlocker for Windows Microsoft windows 10; VeraCrypt or FileVault for Mac).
• Restricted data will not be shared with anyone else unless that person also submits a Restricted Data Use Agreement and obtains approval from the SRSS project.
• If a review by the IRB or Human Subjects Review Committee is required, that review will have already taken place prior to a request for use of any restricted data held by the SRSS project.

Upon completion of your research project, you agree to delete all SRSS data by removing the data from all servers (including email), computers, and any electronic storage devices.
• If changes in computer environment, institution/affiliation, or reason for analysis occur, it is the responsibility of the Principal ‐Investigator to contact the SRSS project. All changes must be noted and approved by the SRSS project before further analysis may continue.
• We request that you share results of your analyses with the SRSS Study Principal Investigator Desiree W. Murray.

fields.value: Self-Regulation Skills for Success Study: Child Level Dataset

dsDescriptionValue.value:
These data include child characteristics and multi-method outcome data evaluating the effectiveness of the Incredible Years Dina Dinosaur small group intervention as delivered in schools to first and second graders. Outcome data include direct child assessment, observation, teacher report, and parent report. The dataset is structured by child ID.

[RESTRICTED DATA]
SRSS Restricted Data Request Process

The documentation is publicly accessible, but the data files are available only upon request. If you would like to gain access to the data in this study, please submit a request by clicking on the “Request Access” link to the right of the dataset in the Files section. Requests can only be made by registered Dataverse users. If you do not have a Dataverse account, please create one and log-in before making your request. After clicking on the "Request Access" link, please download the following SRSS Study Restricted Data Use Agreement and e-mail a completed version to Dr. Desiree Murray at dmurray@childtrends.org. Once your request has been submitted and the completed form emailed, Dr. Murray will review it and follow-up with you by email.

If you have any questions or concerns, please e-mail Dr. Murray at dmurray@childtrends.org. If Dr. Murray is unavailable, please contact Dr. LaForett at laforett@unc.edu

Thank you,
Desiree Murray, PhD
